23 (1) "On-bill credit" means a kilowatt-hour credit applied to a subscribing customer's account to
24 offset the consumption of electrical energy.
25 (2) "Person" means an individual, firm, partnership, company, association, corporation, city, town,
26 or local government entity or any other state, federal, or private entity, whether organized for profit or not.
27 (3) (a) "Public utility" means an electric utility regulated by the commission pursuant to Title 69,
28 chapter 3, on [the effective date of this act], including the public utility's successors or assignees.
